# AgentGuard project rules for Cursor AI

## Project context
AgentGuard: Python security middleware for multi-agent AI systems.
Intercepts inter-agent messages and enforces inspection, trust, and capability controls.

## Language and style
- Python 3.11 only. Use modern syntax (match statements, | union types)
- All public functions and classes must have type annotations (mypy strict)
- Docstrings on all public API surfaces (Google style)
- Line length: 100 characters max

## Security rules — NEVER violate these
- ALWAYS use PyNaCl for cryptographic signing. hashlib is for audit chaining only.
- NEVER use os.system() or subprocess with shell=True in library code
- NEVER log message payloads — only hashes and metadata
- ALWAYS validate manifest YAML against JSON Schema before use

## Architecture rules
- firewall.py entry point must remain under 150 lines
- Each security layer must be independently testable
- Adapters import from agentguard.firewall only
- No circular imports between modules

## Testing rules
- Every module needs a corresponding test in tests/
- Attack fixture tests live in tests/test_integration.py
- Use pytest.mark.asyncio for async tests
